  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Conditions for Ecotourism in Svaneti Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the Improving Conditions for Ecotourism in Svaneti Region Project, Heifer Georgia will provide 20 riding horses to the Svaneti Tourism Centre for home trekking ecotourism activities, improving the economic conditions of four communities of Mestia municipality in the Svaneti Region in Northwest Georgia. In this area, horse trekking routes are already established and marked. In the first year of the project period, 15 pregnant mares will be given to 15 families trained in ecotourism and horse trekking. In the second year, five additional families will join the project. During the third and fourth years of the project, Passing on the Gift (POG) of 20 horses will take place. In addition to original and POG project participants, 40 non-animal recipient project participants will be trained in ecotourism. The trainings will be especially useful for these people, as they already own horses, but the lack of knowledge in ecotourism prevents them from running horse trekking businesses in the area. The trainings will, therefore, open doors for them to new business opportunities. A total of 80 families will receive trainings in Heifer&#x2019;s 12 Cornerstones, horse keeping, horse trekking and ecotourism development.</narrative>
  </description>
